author: MSNBC.com
title: ‘It doesn’t have to be this way’: Chris shares his thoughts before Election Day
description: “It doesn’t have to be this way,” says Chris Hayes, “That's really what it's about. We are masters of our own fate. We control our destiny collectively as a democracy and we can make things better than they are. And that's the civic faith we all have to keep.”
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Julián Castro discusses the ‘metamorphosis of Texas’ amid 2020 election
description: In Texas, more votes have been cast for president so far than in all of 2016. “You’re watching the metamorphosis of Texas,” says Julián Castro, discussing what is shaping up to be a competitive race.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Joy Reid: 'Everything we care about is on the line in this election'
description: We’re less than 4 days away from Election Day and Joy wants to make sure you vote: "Vote for all people who were denied for centuries this basic right of citizenship."
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: ER Doc on Trump’s conspiracy against doctors: ‘A bald-faced brazen lie’
description: Reacting to Trump’s baseless claim that doctors get more money from COVID-19 deaths, Dr. Stephen Sample calls Trump, “the biggest bald-faced brazen liar that’s ever set foot in that Office.”
source.name: MSNBC

title: Rate of Covid-19 deaths leaves hospital workers traumatized
description: Joey Traywick, a Montana ICU nurse, describes how the amount of death his hospital has seen from Covid-19 has left him and his colleagues "broken."

title: Are you suffering from 2020 election burnout? You're not alone.
description: Covid-19 depleted our bodies’ ability to process stress months ago. Then election season arrived.

author: MSNBC.com
title: Actor Sean Connery dead at 90
description: Legendary Actor Sean Connery has died at the age of 90. Connery captured hearts around the world as the first Bond, James Bond, and would go on to star in numerous films throughout his distinguished career.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Olivia Troye: ‘I was asked to write a report for the Vice President’s office saying COVID was over’
description: Olivia Troye, a former COVID Taskforce advisor to Vice President Pence, says the White House has been trying to “wrap up” the pandemic since late springtime and asked her to write a report declaring victory over the virus.
source.name: MSNBC

title: Jarrett on why Obama is joining Biden on the campaign trail now
description: President Barack Obama is ‘the closer’ who can make the best case for Joe Biden and Kamala Harris to win the 2020 presidential election and White House, former Obama Senior Advisor Valerie Jarrett says.
